 President Donald Trump Says He Won’t Attend Joe Biden’s Inauguration United States President Donald Trump has said  on Friday that he won’t attending President-elect Joe Biden’s inauguration on Jan. 20 after admitting defeat in the wake of his supporters storming the US Capitol. Trump Tweeted “To all of those who have asked, I will not be going to the Inauguration on January 20th.” To all of those who have asked, I will not be going to the Inauguration on January 20th. — Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) January 8, 2021 He will be the first incumbent president in 152 years to skip his successor’s swearing-in ceremony. Vice President Mike Pence, however, is expected to attend.